  "body": "### Overview\r\nConvert coverage data from the current Brownie format into the [Cobertura XML spec](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cobertura/web/master/htdocs/xml/coverage-04.dtd) so it may be uploaded and displayed on www.codecov.io.\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\n* Must work for both Solidity and Vyper source files\r\n* Must be compatible with `xdist`\r\n* Must be handle both statement and branch coverage - statements may be translated to lines\r\n* Must be able to include previously calculated coverage data, when the `--update` flag is used\r\n\r\nBecause of Solidity's inheritance logic, the file structure for a given project should be modified as such that `contractName` becomes a directory containing each source file that makes up the compiled contract. For example, [`contracts/LiquidGasToken.sol`](https://github.com/matnad/liquid-gas-token/blob/master/contracts/LiquidGasToken.sol) would be represented as:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontracts/LiquidGasToken/LiquidGasToken.sol\r\ncontracts/LiquidGasToken/LiquidERC20.sol\r\ncontracts/LiquidGasToken/ERC20PointerSupply.sol\r\ncontracts/LiquidGasToken/SafeMath.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n* Coverage data is generated on a per-tx basis and aggregated by functions in [`brownie/test/overage.py`](https://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie/blob/master/brownie/test/coverage.py).\r\n* The final report is saved by a pytest hook in one of the [`brownie/test/managers`](https://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie/tree/master/brownie/test/managers) modules.\r\n* The data format is specified in the [documentation](https://eth-brownie.readthedocs.io/en/stable/build-folder.html#test-results-and-coverage-data)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Completion Goals\r\n1. XML formatter that produces reports understood by codecov\r\n2. Test cases that generate and verify XML outputs using the pytest's `testdir` fixture. See the existing [plugin tests](https://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie/tree/master/tests/test).",
